rComments: Ajax is a very kind and caring Professor who listens to his students and cares about them. The midterm was 3 essay style questions picked from a bank of questions available to students so it is easy to prepare for. The final was partially multiple choice and 2 questions in the same format as the midterm. Overall, Ajax is a good professor.

Prof Ajax is the BEST for making his students work super hard. You will be DISCUSSING in class a lot! So you have to read chapters before and come to class with some REAL LIFE EXAMPLES. LISTEN to what he says in class, WRITE DOWN what you also hear from your classmates. Everything from the discussion is very important and it will be on your tests.

Terrible professor, doesn't teach during the lectures, instead just asks students to answer questions from their perspective and I don't think I've ever heard him say someone is wrong so it becomes so vague what he is looking for. Avoid at all costs

You should attend class as he gives practice MCQ questions for exams. Start the group project early and book consultations with him as he will tell you where you need to pay attention to. You need to take materials from both the textbook and his slides in order to do well in the course
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Group projects']

rComments: Final exam was 18 straight chapters.

Extremely vague explanation on most of the materials, so you are better off reading the textbook than going to the lectures. The course deliverables require a lot of work and the prof mark them so hard that I feel like I am taking a MBA program instead of a BCom. Go to a better prof if you can.

He is extremely funny prof as he jokes, but his teaching will not help you ACE the course deliverables. If you want to do well, then read the textbook thoroughly and understand everything in it. Lectures are completely useless since the prof rephrase everything from the book. Watch a few episodes of Spongebob to kill time, don't do useless lectures

teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: This professor has attitude problems since he constantly makes jokes in serious situations and never provides any resources to help prepare for the exams. Terrible experience. He has no idea about how to teach. Require a large amount of reading.

I cannot believe that I paid thousands to hear a guy talking jokes. He is probably one of the most unprofessional teachers that I have ever encountered. The class materials were very unclear and his lectures did nothing to improve your understanding of the concepts. If you enrol in this course, be prepared to have panic attack.

He does not take his job seriously since he makes jokes in serious occasions all the time. The assignments and exams are not relevant to the class materials and he seldom reaches out to help his students. Avoid this tough grader.

Mister Ajax was the worst prof I've had since being here. He doesn't care about his students and is extremely rude. If you send him an email get ready to receive one back in a rude and unprofessional matter.

His quizzes were the hardest things I have ever written since I came to this university, they had time limit and they were not based on the textbook questions. The group projects were fine but both midterm and final were totally unfair. Most of the questions would leave you wonder if you had actually taken this class.
He didn't know how to teach properly.

The prof treated the class as a joke since he didn't teach seriously throughout the entire semester. His lectures were different from the PPT posted on Brightspace and online quizzes were difficult and time-limited. The final was a total disaster with no ideas of what was going on. Anyway, he turned an easy course into an impossible course.
teacherRatingTags: ['Hilarious', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Prof Ajax has a funny and hilarious personality, but the class itself was really helpless. His lecture slides were different from the ones posted on BrightSpace, which made the class really confusing since the differences were really huge. Also, put 30 minutes limit on quizzes and made them really hard and out of context. Remember, textbook is key.

Group projects were marked fairly but the quizzes and midterm werent. The quizzes were very specific out of the book and had a time limit while the final exam hardly covered any class material ( asked us stuff from managerial and econ?). This class overall was too much work and not graded right. Hes a funny guy and pr0vides good feedback/help tho
The prof made the quizzes and final extremely vague and difficult, midterm was not that hard but far from an easy one. However, there is no denying that his jokes were somewhat funny.

Extremely good at telling jokes during the lecture so that nobody will think his class is boring. The prof has a really good attitude towards every student, and you will realise that he is a nice person when he walks into the classroom with a big smile. I strongly recommend this prof if you think school is boring.

rComments: Nice and funny guy, helps a lot for group projects. But this class was torture. Lectures were so scattered and made no sense. Midterm questions were given beforehand, which helped, but the questions were still broad and weird. He gave 5 quizzes which were really hard and the final was difficult too; really vague, subjective questions. Would avoid.

The final exam questions were really vague and unclear, the prof made them like all the choices were seemingly correct, which is tough. The prof is funny but not helpful when it comes to quizzes and exams. Consider this is a compulsory course, just get everything done and dont expect to have an A+ for this class, then you will be fine.

This guy is a very funny man. But I don't go to school for comedy. I'm in accounting, and yet this is my hardest class. The quizzes were unnecessarily difficult. Midterm wasn't the worst, but also unnecessarily hard. And the final? Absolute garbage. Felt like there were no proper resources. Nice guy, but this class was awful.

This prof is great! BUT the course isn't all that easy, it's not like drinking water you need to study so if you're not required to take this course and looking for an easy mark then I would take something else

The prof is generally a funny and kind guy. However, when it comes to quizzes and the midterm, you are on your own since his lectures have nothing to do with the quizzes and midterm. Also, waste two lectures' time to let us present what we write for the project, which is pretty pointless.

the midterm was hard; I went to all the classes, took notes, did all the work and still got a C. The material was easy but the actual midterm was impossible; 3 specific questions worth 15 marks each - and he gave us 26 questions to study. its all memory. He's good at explaining things but his quizzes and tests are too hard, scared for the final
Quizzes are too hard. And does not relevant to the textbook and the lecture.

He's is a good prof in general and a funny man. But he's midterm and online quizzes are super hard! He posted the midterm questions at the beginning of the semester. just imagine how hard are they. If u wanna learn, he is the one, but If u wanna get a higher grade, he's not your choice.
Professor Ajax was really helpful in his office hours and is always open to meet. He gives great guidance for the projects and assignments.

HANDS DOWN... This is one of the best courses in Telfer. He's my favourite prof that I've had thus far. I would STRONGLY recommend taking AJAX's class!!! One of the easiest classes to pass and so much fun!

Took this class 2 years ago before switching to science. One of my favourite and most memorable profs, and was really entertaining to be in his lecture. Cares a lot about students' success and extremely accessible outside of class-- i definitely visited frequently during office hours. All in all, really nice guy and passionate about his field!

Ajax is a great prof if you're looking to learn, however, his midterm (2 essay style questions) were very difficult. Although he had a bonus question which really increased the class average. He is an easy marker. I would recommend this professor. His multiple choice are however, very difficult. there are a lot of opportunities to get a good grade

One of the best professors at Telfer. If you go to class he will provide you with midterm and exam hints and if you visit his office hours he will layout both group assignments. Also, conveys information with real life material and lots of jokes. Highly recommend over any other Marketing professors.

Maybe it was harder in the past, but over the past few years he's been teaching with VERY clear expectations of what he wants done by students. Amazing lectures and stories, really enjoys what he does and it shows as he's really good at it! Go to class, listen and you'll really enjoy his lectures!
Persaud is simply awesome.  Really nice guy and cares. Definitely pick Ajax if you are taking marketing.

Really good prof! He keeps class  interesting, tells jokes and although the lectures closely reflect the text he explains more thoroughly in class so its best to go. Tests are difficult but if you take the time to go see him to review and ask for help he genuinely cares and will help you achieve the grade you're looking for. Definitely recommend!!
He makes marketing so interesting that I would actually consider switching out of finance!

He is a good prof but the course material is boring as hell. There were two huge group projects that were very time consuming. He is funny and makes a lot of jokes during class, and he also cares quite a lot about his teaching. Beware of the final, it was 90% multiple choices but extremely hard.
Ajax is the best prof i have ever had. He is great! he does want people to participate by giving answers but normally they are common sense. Would highly recommend to anyone taking marketing.

I loved Ajax! He was such a nice guy, took the time to get to know everyone. Still one of the easiest courses though, and if you go to Ajax's office hours he'll really help you out!!

There is no point in going to class since the topics he brings up are irrelevant to the exams although attendance is mandatory. Just read the textbook instead

Makes a lot of dirty jokes. The course load was quite heavy with connect assignments due every week. Midterm was two very broad(vague) essay questions and exam was difficult multiple choice questions.
Decent prof. Really loves what he does and that comes through. I mostly just studied trigger words and put decent effort into assignments.

Tough class, but only because he asks you questions that make sure you really understand the material in a real world setting instead of just memorize it. Not a very good prof and his lecture style is very unorganized and hard to follow along. I would avoid if possible. The textbook is 100% necessary because going to class is almost pointless. Does not convey the subject well at all, although he knows the stuff well

When he marks he doesn't give marks for information you input, he takes marks off for the information you missed, because of this combined with his question style it is very easy to lose marks.

12 Learn Smart modules. 6 online quizzes. 2 group projects. 2 mid-terms (which are worth less the the open book quizzes and modules). 4 Marketer's showdown cases.
